sequenceDiagram
    participant User as "End User"
    participant Librarian as "Librarian"
    participant Administrator as "Library Administrator"
    participant Authentication as "Authentication Service"
    participant Analytics as "Data Analytics Service"
    participant Database as "Database"
    participant Server as "SmartLibrary Server"
    participant Client as "Web Browser"

    User->>Client: Login Request
    Client->>Server: Login Request
    Server->>Authentication: Authenticate User
    Authentication-->>Server: Authentication Response
    Server->>Database: Retrieve User Data
    Database-->>Server: User Data
    Server-->>Client: Login Response
    Client-->>User: Login Response

    Librarian->>Client: Search Book Request
    Client->>Server: Search Book Request
    Server->>Database: Retrieve Book Data
    Database-->>Server: Book Data
    Server-->>Client: Search Book Response
    Client-->>Librarian: Search Book Response

    Administrator->>Client: Upload CSV/Excel File
    Client->>Server: Upload CSV/Excel File
    Server->>Database: Store File Data
    Database-->>Server: File Data Stored
    Server-->>Client: Upload Response
    Client-->>Administrator: Upload Response

    Server->>Analytics: Send Data for Analytics
    Analytics-->>Server: Analytics Response
    Server->>Client: Update Dashboard
    Client-->>User: Updated Dashboard

    User->>Client: Request Report
    Client->>Server: Request Report
    Server->>Database: Retrieve Report Data
    Database-->>Server: Report Data
    Server->>Client: Report Response
    Client-->>User: Report Response

    Note over Client,Server: HTTPS used for secure communication
    Note over Client,Server: WebSockets used for real-time updates
    activate Server
    Server->>Client: Real-time Updates
    deactivate Server